                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>A large thick tablet of coarse yellow stone, intact on all sides, but missing the upper right corner. The stone is thicker at the base. The rear is rough and uneven.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.sandstone" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/75.html">sandstone</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259">plaque</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">44</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">59.5</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">9-18</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.complete"/>
		    </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>The text is set over two lines, neither fully centred, nor fully aligned to the left, on the upper half of the front face of the stone.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                	<damage ana="#text_condition.complete"/>
			</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Wide square letter forms, simple deep strokes without serifs. Alpha with broken bar; epsilon variously has shorter middle bar (1st and 3rd) or strokes of equal length (2nd); M has vertical first and last strokes, with the middle strokes only descending halfway; sigma has parallel top and bottom strokes, with variable middle strokes.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line2">Line 1-2</locus>
                                <dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <height unit="mm">50-65</height>
                                </dimensions>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line2">Interlineation line 1 to 2</locus>
                                <dimensions type="interlinear">
                                    <height unit="mm"/>
                                </dimensions>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
